premise_source_doc_sentence: The Thénardiers , commonly known as Monsieur Thénardier  (  -LSB- təˈnɑrdi.eɪ -RSB- -LSB- tenaʁdje -RSB-  )  and Madame Thénardier , are fictional characters , the secondary antagonists in Victor Hugo 's 1862 novel Les Misérables and in many adaptations of the novel into other media .
